rows: RMWD holds YYoront /pirri/ 'emu' (< *purriwi) to be a loan from this.
Dyirbal is the most likely source. pPaman *kungkaka.
Eastern, from Flinders Island south; includes Dyirrbal etc.
Both are loans; /yàrramán/ from some languge to the south.
Ctenophorus isolepis, Diporiphora spp., Lophognathus spp.
